author: Inside Edition
description: Candice Dodge and her dad, Brian, were cheering on the Buffalo Bills when suddenly, Brian collapsed, his heart not beating. Candice needed her cries for help to be heard above the roar of the crowd. That's when the highly spirited Buffalo Bills fans, lovingly known as the "Bills Mafia," stepped in. Nurse Danielle Johnson heard the cries for help and started giving Brian chest compressions. Two minutes later, Brian regained consciousness. The 68-year-old dad spoke with Inside Edition.
title: Hero Nurse Saves Man's Life After Health Emergency At NFL Game

author: Inside Edition
description: A man woke a sleeping family when their house caught fire and then disappeared. In doorbell footage, the hero is seen holding the family's little boy in his arms as they fled the flames. Then, the hero helped another youngster and the rest of the family to safety. Lilliana Quesada says she owes her family's lives to the good Samaritan. Quesada is making a public appeal for the hero to come forward. There are clues to his identity. The family's GoFundMe can be found here: https://bit.ly/3J9E5pF
title: Who Is This Good Samaritan Who Saved Family From Apartment Fire?

author: Inside Edition
description: President Donald Trump received a hero's welcome as he strode into the Israeli parliament. Trump's speech was aired live on all the networks. There was one moment of chaos when far-left members of the Knesset interrupted. The protestors were swiftly hauled away. From Israel, Trump flew to Egypt for a peace summit. His peace-making efforts are being hailed across the globe Monday, even from those not usually known to praise Trump.
title: Donald Trump Receives Hero's Welcome at Israeli Parliament

author: Inside Edition
description: In the last few months, Diane Keaton's health started to decline. Close friend and songwriter Carole Bayer Sager and record producer Jonas Myrin worked with Keaton last November on a holiday song called "First Christmas." Making music was one of Keaton's final wishes. Inside Edition spoke to them in the same room where Keaton recorded the song. Keaton's career spanned nearly six decades. She made a name for herself playing Al Pacino's love interest in "The Godfather."
title: Reflecting On The Life Of Icon Diane Keaton

author: Inside Edition
description: A homecoming dance was cancelled at a New Jersey high school, but it wasn't adults raining on the students' parade. The Wall Township High School reportedly cancelled the event because of low ticket sales. Some students told WCBS why they aren't interested in participating in this teenage ritual. A psychologist says schools should rethink their social events to get students to participate. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: High School Dances Going Extinct? NJ School Cancels Dance Due To Lack Of Interest

author: Inside Edition
description: A former rock star serving a lengthy prison sentence for child sex offenses was reportedly killed in prison. The BBC says Ian Watkins, former frontman of the Welsh band Lostprophets was fatally injured at Wakefield Prison over the weekend. Watkins, 48, was sentenced in 2013 to 29 years in prison for sexually abusing children, including the attempted rape of a baby, according to the judgment against him. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Ian Watkins, Former Rock Star Who Sexually Abused Children, Killed In Prison

author: Inside Edition
description: Shelby Edge from North Carolina is battling a rare disease that makes eating uncomfortable and almost impossible.
title: Woman Has Disease That Makes Eating Almost Impossible #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Cops in Ohio had a hard time getting this suspect to cooperate. A giant inflatable pumpkin got loose from a lawn and started rolling down the streets in Parma Heights. An officer saw it make a getaway and decided to chase after it. Working together they tried to roll the wayward gourd into the back of a patrol car. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Cops Struggle To Wrangle Rolling Giant Inflatable Pumpkin

author: Inside Edition
description: Ed Gein and his unspeakable crimes were the inspiration for horror movie classics "Psycho," "The Texas Chainsaw Massacre," and "The Silence of the Lambs."
title: 'Monster: The Ed Gein Story' Is Massive Hit On Netflix #shorts
